<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-07-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-07-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="103" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d103">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 180/43.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Pierrepont</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-07-09"><hi rend="italic">July 9,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Pierrepont reports that executive authority was transferred on this
                            date by the President of Chile to Elias Fernandez Albano as vice
                            president, and says the President will leave on July 14, on the cruiser
                                <hi rend="italic">Esmeralda</hi>, for Panama.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>